President Donald Trump has made several nominations and appointments to key positions in his administration. John Ullyot has been appointed as Assistant Secretary of Veterans Affairs (Public and Intergovernmental Affairs). Ullyot has previously held senior communications positions and served as a Director of Communications for the United States Senate Armed Services Committee and the United States Senate Veterans' Affairs Committee. He has a background in intelligence and served in the United States Marine Corps.

Trump has also announced his intent to nominate Kevin McAleenan as Commissioner of U.S. Customs and Border Protection at the Department of Homeland Security. McAleenan has been the Deputy Commissioner since 2014 and has played a key role in developing strategies to protect the nation's borders and combat transnational criminal networks. He has received several awards for his work, including the Presidential Rank Award.

Additionally, Mira Ricardel has been nominated to serve as Under Secretary of Commerce for Export Administration. Ricardel has a background in national security and has held various positions within the Department of Defense. She has also worked in the private sector, holding senior leadership positions at Boeing Defense Space and Security. Ricardel has a Bachelor of Science in Foreign Service from Georgetown University.

These nominations and appointments are subject to confirmation by the Senate.